K\in\mathbb{R}^+
x\ge 1
\left|\int_{1}^x \sin(t+t^7)dt \right|<K
f(x) = x + x^7
g(t)
[0,\infty)
t \to \infty
\int_0^x \sin(x + x^7)\ dx = \int_0^{f(x)} \sin(t) g'(t)\ dt
g(t) = t^{1/7} - \dfrac{1}{7} t^{-5/7} + O(t^{-11/7})
g'(t) = \dfrac{1}{7 g(t)^6 + 1} =  \dfrac{1}{7} t^{-6/7} + O(t^{-12/7})
\int_1^\infty |\sin(t)| t^{-12/7}\ dt < \infty
 \int_1^R \sin(t) t^{-6/7}\ dt = \left. - \cos(t) t^{-6/7} \right|_1^R -  \dfrac{6}{7} \int_1^R \cos(t) t^{-13/7}\ dt
